           ------
           Charset checking
           ------
	
How to enable automatic charset checking against an expected charset. 
	
	To enable automatic charset checking against an expected charset you must define a JVM property named "<<HIBERNATE_VALIDATOR_SECURITY_CONTRIBS_EXPECTED_CHARSET>>" with a value setted to the charset named expected (case is not sensitive):
	
	Example:
	
+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+		
HIBERNATE_VALIDATOR_SECURITY_CONTRIBS_EXPECTED_CHARSET=UTF-8

HIBERNATE_VALIDATOR_SECURITY_CONTRIBS_EXPECTED_CHARSET=UTF-16LE

HIBERNATE_VALIDATOR_SECURITY_CONTRIBS_EXPECTED_CHARSET=ISO-8859-1
+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+		
		
	[]
	
	See {{{http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/nio/charset/Charset.html}here}} for a complete charset name list.
			